---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-coverage', text: 'Plans and Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pros-and-cons', text: 'Pros and Cons', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-and-service', text: 'Claims and Service', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who It\'s For', level: 2 },
  { id: 'alternatives', text: 'Alternatives to Consider', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomads Guide', href: '/insurance-for/digital-nomads' },
  { title: 'IMG in Mexico', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance/img-global' },
  { title: 'IMG in Costa Rica', href: '/countries/costa-rica/insurance/img-global' },
  { title: 'IMG in Portugal', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance/img-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'limit', header: 'Lifetime Max' },
  { key: 'outpatient', header: 'Outpatient' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Bronze', limit: '$1 million', outpatient: 'Limited', bestFor: 'Basic coverage' },
  { plan: 'Silver', limit: '$5 million', outpatient: 'Included', bestFor: 'Good value' },
  { plan: 'Gold', limit: '$5 million', outpatient: 'Enhanced', bestFor: 'Comprehensive' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', limit: '$8 million', outpatient: 'Premium', bestFor: 'Maximum coverage' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="IMG Global Review"
  description="In-depth review of IMG Global Medical international health insurance. Coverage options, pricing, pros and cons for expats and digital nomads."
  headline="IMG Global Medical Insurance Review"
  subheadline="A detailed look at IMG's plans, pricing, and why they're popular with budget-conscious expats."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an IMG Global Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    IMG (International Medical Group) has been providing international health insurance for over 30 years. They've built a reputation as one of the most affordable options for expats and digital nomads who want solid medical coverage without premium pricing.
  </p>
  <p>
    With their parent company SiriusPoint rated A- (Excellent) by A.M. Best, and BBB accreditation since 2005, IMG offers financial stability alongside competitive pricing. Their 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating from over 19,000 reviews reflects strong customer satisfaction.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Quick Facts</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
      <li><strong>Headquarters:</strong> Indianapolis, USA</li>
      <li><strong>Years in Business:</strong> 30+</li>
      <li><strong>Financial Rating:</strong> A- (Excellent) via SiriusPoint</li>
      <li><strong>Plan Types:</strong> Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum</li>
      <li><strong>Maximum Coverage:</strong> Up to $8 million (Platinum)</li>
      <li><strong>Age Limit:</strong> Up to 74 to enroll</li>
      <li><strong>Trustpilot Rating:</strong> 4.6/5 stars (19,000+ reviews)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Personalized Quote"
    description="See what IMG Global would cost for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="plans-and-coverage">Plans and Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global Medical Insurance offers four plan tiers with increasing coverage limits. All plans are fully customizable with multiple deductible options and optional add-ons.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Core Coverage (All Plans)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Inpatient hospital care</li>
    <li>Emergency medical treatment</li>
    <li>Surgery and anesthesia</li>
    <li>Prescription medications</li>
    <li>Cancer treatment</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation</li>
    <li>Repatriation of remains</li>
    <li>24/7 assistance services</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Coverage Areas</h3>
  <p>Choose your geographic coverage:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Worldwide:</strong> Full global coverage including the US</li>
    <li><strong>Worldwide excluding US:</strong> Significant savings if you don't need US coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Europe:</strong> Regional coverage at lower rates</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deductible Options</h3>
  <p>
    IMG offers seven deductible choices: $250, $500, $1,000, $2,500, $5,000, and $10,000. Higher deductibles significantly reduce premiums.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Bonus:</strong> 50% of your deductible is waived for treatment outside the US. So a $2,500 deductible becomes just $1,250 out-of-pocket for care abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>Optional Add-Ons</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dental:</strong> Routine and major dental coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Vision:</strong> Eye exams and glasses/contacts</li>
    <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Pregnancy and childbirth (waiting period applies)</li>
    <li><strong>Terrorism coverage:</strong> Protection in high-risk areas</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Unique Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Travel Intelligence:</strong> Push notifications with location-specific alerts for crime, terrorism, severe weather, and other threats</li>
    <li><strong>Direct billing:</strong> IMG identifies providers who bill directly, reducing out-of-pocket costs</li>
    <li><strong>Multilingual support:</strong> Staff speaks 18 languages</li>
    <li><strong>Global Senior Plan:</strong> Automatic transition option at age 75 with no additional underwriting</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    IMG is known for competitive pricing, especially compared to premium providers like BUPA and Cigna. The combination of multiple deductible options and coverage area choices lets you dial in the right price.
  </p>

  <h3>Sample Annual Premiums (Age 40, $250 deductible, Worldwide ex-US)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Silver: ~$2,800/year ($235/month)</li>
    <li>Gold: ~$4,500/year ($375/month)</li>
    <li>Platinum: ~$7,500/year ($625/month)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Sample Annual Premiums (Age 32, $1,000 deductible, Worldwide ex-US)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Silver: ~$1,500/year ($125/month)</li>
    <li>Gold: ~$2,400/year ($200/month)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <em>Prices vary by age, coverage area, and exact plan configuration. These are estimates for illustration.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Payment Options</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Annual:</strong> Best value (no surcharge)</li>
    <li><strong>Semi-annual:</strong> 10% surcharge</li>
    <li><strong>Quarterly:</strong> 12% surcharge</li>
    <li><strong>Monthly:</strong> 20% surcharge</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Pay annually if possible—the monthly surcharge adds up to 20% more over the year.
  </p>

  <h3>Ways to Save</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductible:</strong> $5,000+ deductibles cut premiums substantially</li>
    <li><strong>Exclude US/Canada:</strong> Removing North America saves hundreds annually</li>
    <li><strong>Pay annually:</strong> Avoid 10-20% payment surcharges</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Europe-only costs less than worldwide</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="See Your Actual Price"
    description="IMG's quote tool makes it easy to compare options."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="pros-and-cons">Pros and Cons</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Pros</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Excellent customer reviews (4.6/5, 19K+ reviews)</li>
        <li>Very competitive pricing</li>
        <li>Flexible deductible options (7 choices)</li>
        <li>50% deductible waived outside US</li>
        <li>Up to $8 million coverage (Platinum)</li>
        <li>Easy-to-use website and quote process</li>
        <li>Direct billing with many providers</li>
        <li>Travel Intelligence safety alerts</li>
        <li>Multilingual support (18 languages)</li>
        <li>Path to coverage at 75+ (Global Senior Plan)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Cons</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
        <li>Claims processing can be slow (weeks to months)</li>
        <li>Short free look period (3 days vs 10-21 elsewhere)</li>
        <li>No trip interruption/cancellation coverage</li>
        <li>Monthly payments add 20% to cost</li>
        <li>Can't lower deductible at renewal</li>
        <li>Account/renewal process frustrations reported</li>
        <li>Not ideal for adventure sports</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="claims-and-service">Claims and Service</h2>

  <h3>Filing Claims</h3>
  <p>
    IMG offers online claims submission through their website and mobile app. They also provide direct billing arrangements with providers worldwide to reduce your out-of-pocket expenses.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Important note:</strong> While IMG's overall customer satisfaction is high, some reviewers mention slow claims processing. Expect several weeks for reimbursement, and potentially longer for complex claims. Document everything and follow up regularly.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    IMG provides 24/7/365 assistance with:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>In-house nurses, doctors, and case managers</li>
    <li>Multilingual support (18 languages)</li>
    <li>Emergency evacuation coordination</li>
    <li>Provider location assistance</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Customer reviews consistently praise the website's ease of use for quotes and policy management, though some mention challenges with the live chat support.
  </p>

  <h3>Pre-Existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    IMG uses standard underwriting for pre-existing conditions. Coverage depends on your health history—conditions may be covered, excluded, or subject to waiting periods. Be thorough and honest on your application.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who It's For</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global may be a good fit if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Want solid coverage at affordable prices</li>
    <li>Prefer flexible deductible options</li>
    <li>Don't need US/Canada coverage (biggest savings)</li>
    <li>Are a digital nomad or long-term expat</li>
    <li>Want an easy quote and enrollment process</li>
    <li>Value the 50% deductible waiver outside the US</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    It may not be ideal if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Need fast claims reimbursement</li>
    <li>Want trip cancellation/interruption coverage</li>
    <li>Do extreme or adventure sports regularly</li>
    <li>Prefer premium service over budget pricing</li>
    <li>Need to change your deductible at renewal</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="alternatives">Alternatives to Consider</h2>
  <p>
    If IMG Global doesn't seem like the right fit, consider these alternatives:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> More premium service and larger network, higher prices. <a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Similar flexibility, competitive pricing. <a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Premium coverage with excellent mental health benefits. <a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Even more budget-friendly, but less comprehensive (travel medical vs health insurance)</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Compare?"
    description="See how IMG Global compares to other options for your needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This review is for informational purposes only. Plan details, pricing, and availability change frequently. We are not affiliated with IMG and are not insurance brokers. Verify all information directly with IMG before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
